## ğŸ“‚ Files in this Repository
- **`Ecommerce sales dashboard project.pbix`** â†’ The main Power BI file containing the data model, transformations, and dashboard.  
- **`Orders.csv`** â†’ Customer and order details (`Order ID`, `Order Date`, `Customer Name`, `State`, `City`).  
- **`Details.csv`** â†’ Item-level details (`Order ID`, `Amount`, `Profit`, `Quantity`, `Category`, `Sub-Category`, `Payment Mode`).  
- **`dark-gradient.jpg`** â†’ Dashboard background image for better visual design.  

## ğŸš€ Key Features
- ğŸ“ˆ **Sales & Profit Analysis** â†’ Track total sales and profit over time.  
- ğŸ›ï¸ **Product Performance** â†’ Insights by `Category` and `Sub-Category`.  
- ğŸ—ºï¸ **Geographical Insights** â†’ Sales distribution across states.  
- ğŸ’³ **Payment Method Trends** â†’ Breakdown of sales by payment mode.  
- ğŸ›ï¸ **Interactive Filters** â†’ Slicers & filters to drill down into specific data points.  

## âš¡ How to Use
1. **Clone the Repository**  
   git clone https://github.com/kondukarthik/Ecommerce-sales-analysis-using-power-bi-dashboard.git
2. **Open in Power BI Desktop**
   Launch the `Ecommerce sales dashboard project.pbix` file in **Power BI Desktop**.
3. **Refresh Data (if needed)**
   If file paths differ, update the data source paths for `Orders.csv` and `Details.csv` in **Power Query Editor**.
4. **Explore**
   Interact with the dashboard to uncover business insights.

